  "management45": "Critical operational constraints are flagged at 32 airports right now. No engine anti-ice operations are currently flagged. Across base airports: 17 critical, 5 high, 9 medium, 8 normal. Key bases needing attention include Copernicus Wrocław (WRO/EPWR), Cluj Avram Iancu (CLJ/LRCL) and Chişinău (RMO/LUKK); plus 19 other bases. 9 additional base airports are at medium severity and should be monitored closely. At base airports, the dominant pattern is snow-related runway contamination risk, mist and cold‑temperature performance penalties  — most notably around Bucharest Henri Coandă (OTP/LROP), Bucharest Băneasa Aurel Vlaicu (BBU/LRBS) and Chişinău (RMO/LUKK). Network hotspots: Bucharest Băneasa Aurel Vlaicu (BBU/LRBS), Bucharest Henri Coandă (OTP/LROP), Sofia (SOF/LBSF), Chişinău (RMO/LUKK), Thessaloniki Macedonia (SKG/LGTS) and 27 others. Primary drivers: snow / blowing snow, low cloud base and cold‑temperature performance penalties. Expected impact is reduced runway capacity with higher delay and diversion risk, especially where visibility/RVR and cloud base are very low. Since the last update, 2 airports changed status, led by Almaty (ALA/UAAA), Skopje (SKP/LWSK).",
